    <div class="bio__information">
      <div class="bio__name">Caitlin Fisher</div>
      <div>Head Instructor/Owner</div>
      <p class="bio__description">
        Caitlin Fisher is the owner and head dance instructor of JP Dance Co-op. She founded 
        the school in 2017 to offer community-based dance classes to introduce and inspire 
        young children to dance. Caitlin started dancing at age three and spent her adolescent 
        years dancing and teaching at Paulette's Ballet Studio. Caitlin went on to study modern 
        dance, earning a degree in dance from Roger Williams University. During her time as an 
        undergraduate student, she choreographed for the University's dance club and was a 
        member of its Dance Theatre troupe. In the fall of 2012, Caitlin spent time in London 
        training under Jorge Cresis and Stephen Pelton as part of an exclusive performance-based 
        dance course. Certified from DETC as a dance trainer, Caitlin has taught at a number of 
        local schools, including choreographing for Creative Steps Dance Studio's annual 
        Nutcracker performance. She also spent five years as part of the DanceWorks Boston 
        company, dancing in bi-annual performances. In addition to running JP Dance Co-op, 
        Caitlin currently teaches beginner teen and adult dance classes at Total Eclipse Dance 
        Studio in Needham, MA. 
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

